    "description": "Antalya, where Roman columns rise from turquoise waters and minarets cast shadows over ancient harbors, is a city where history meets the Mediterranean's embrace. The old town's Ottoman houses, with their wooden balconies and red-tiled roofs, cascade down to the sea, while the modern marina's luxury yachts bob beside traditional wooden gulets. The city's soul lives in its çay bahçesis - tea gardens where the scent of apple tobacco mingles with the sound of waves - and in its historic Kaleiçi district where Roman gates open onto narrow streets lined with carpet shops and artisan workshops. From the ancient theater of Aspendos to the waterfalls of Düden, from the ruins of Perge to the beaches of Lara, Antalya's unique charm comes from this perfect blend of ancient history and modern leisure. The city's streets tell stories of Roman emperors and Seljuk sultans, while its modern resorts offer a gateway to both Turkey's rich past and its vibrant present.",
